HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 523
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Amanda Kreh on her
selection as the 2024–2025 Cannon County
School District Grades 9-12 Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Amanda Kreh is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Kreh has been selected as the 2024–2025 Cannon County School
District Grades 9-12 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Amanda Kreh is a French teacher at Cannon County High School, having
taught for twenty-four years in total; in addition to her work in the classroom, she has generously
given of her time to lead her local Girl Scout troop and teach Sunday School at her church; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Kreh's multitudinous talents have serviced varied roles throughout her
career, including as a technology coach, testing coordinator, co-director for after-school
programs, and federal Title II program coordinator; and
WHEREAS, steeping herself in further study to better her teaching, Ms. Kreh graduated
from Auburn University with a Bachelor of Science and master's degrees; and
WHEREAS, she is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who works
assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars and as
citizens; and
